<paragraph blockId="10.[189,1399,1195,1402]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Currently, there are 33 species assigned to this genus (Van Soest 
<emphasis box="[982,1044,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">et al.</emphasis>
2012). Possibly, some of the species may need to be transferred to other genera because of the interpretation of the morphological structure of the chelae (e.g. 
<taxonomicName authority="Levi, 1993" authorityName="Levi" authorityYear="1993" box="[514,737,1267,1293]" class="Demospongiae" family="Esperiopsidae" genus="Esperiopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="flava">
<emphasis box="[514,603,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">E. flava</emphasis>
LÃ©vi, 1993
</taxonomicName>
and similar species with deformed chelae, which cannot be identified with certainty as palmate), others would have to be returned to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vosmaer" authorityYear="1880" box="[1073,1218,1303,1329]" class="Demospongiae" family="Esperiopsidae" genus="Amphilectus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1073,1218,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Amphilectus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
if the style size difference would be no longer a valid discriminatory character of the two genera. Future studies using additional datasets (such as molecular sequences) are needed to clarify the status of 
<taxonomicName box="[1174,1311,1376,1401]" class="Demospongiae" family="Esperiopsidae" genus="Esperiopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1174,1311,1376,1401]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Esperiopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
